HEADWORD: Skillet
<hw>Skil"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>escuelette</ets>, dim. of <ets>escuelle</ets> a porringer, F.
<ets>ecuelle</ets>, fr. L. <ets>scutella</ets>, dim. of
<ets>scutra</ets>, <ets>scuta</ets>, a dish. Cf. <er>Scuttle</er> a
basket.]</ety> <def>A small vessel of iron, copper, or other metal, with
a handle, used for culinary purpose, as for stewing meat.</def>⟦br⟧
